# Malha — Full Pattern System Architecture

## Comprehensive Technical Design Document

---

# 1. Introduction

The Pattern System is the core engine of Malha.

Everything in the application depends on it:

- project execution
    
- row tracking
    
- AI assistance
    
- yarn estimation
    
- pattern adaptation
    
- progress analytics
    
- voice commands
    
- community validation
    
- future AI learning
    

The pattern engine is not a simple document viewer.

It is a:

> structured executable crafting workflow system.

---

# 2. Core Philosophy

Traditional knitting/crochet patterns are:

- inconsistent
    
- human-oriented
    
- ambiguous
    
- difficult to parse
    
- difficult to adapt mathematically
    

Malha transforms patterns into:

- structured workflows
    
- machine-readable execution graphs
    
- validated procedural systems
    

while preserving:

- human readability
    
- original notation
    
- craft authenticity
    

---

# 3. Primary Goals

The system must:

## Human Goals

- feel natural to knitters
    
- preserve traditional notation
    
- remain editable
    
- support multiple languages
    

## Technical Goals

- support progress tracking
    
- support AI interpretation
    
- support mathematical adaptation
    
- support validation
    
- support reusable components
    

---

# 4. Supported Craft Types

Initially:

- knitting
    
- crochet
    

Future:

- tunisian crochet
    
