# 7. Core Pattern Architecture

Patterns use hybrid storage architecture.

---

# Layer 1 — Original Source

Immutable archive layer.

Purpose:

- preserve authenticity
    
- allow reparsing
    
- preserve formatting
    
- legal traceability
    

Example:

```json
{
  "source_id": "pdf_001",
  "source_type": "pdf",
  "language": "pt-PT",
  "original_text": "...",
  "ocr_confidence": 0.92
}
```

---

# Layer 2 — Structured Metadata

Contains global pattern information.

Example categories:

- title
    
- language
    
- craft type
    
- difficulty
    
- size range
    
- gauge
    
- materials
    
- designer
    
- publication year
    

---

# Layer 3 — Execution Graph

The actual procedural knitting logic.

This is the heart of the system.

---

# 8. Why Execution Graphs?

Traditional text:

```text
Decrease 1 stitch every 2 rows 52 times.
```

Machine-readable representation:

```json
{
  "type": "decrease_repeat",
  "repeat_count": 52,
  "every_n_rows": 2,
  "decrease_amount": 1
}
```

Benefits:

- trackable
    
- adaptable
    
- voice-navigable
    
- mathematically verifiable
    

---

