# 13. Stitch Library System

Reusable stitch definitions.

Avoids duplication.

---

## Example

```json
{
  "stitch_id": "shell_pattern_2color",
  "repeat_multiple": 8,
  "instructions": []
}
```

---

# 14. Why Stitch Libraries Matter

Without libraries:

- repeated parsing
    
- inconsistency
    
- poor adaptation
    

With libraries:

- reusable logic
    
- cleaner execution
    
- AI understanding
    
- easier validation
    

---

# 15. Section System

Patterns divided into logical construction sections.

Examples:

- back panel
    
- sleeves
    
- collar
    
- yoke
    

---

## Example

```json
{
  "section_id": "back_panel",
  "name": "Costas"
}
```

---

# 16. Step System

Every section contains ordered procedural steps.

---

# 17. Step Types

Examples:

|Type|Purpose|
|---|---|
|cast_on|initial stitches|
|knit|knit rows|
|purl|purl rows|
|increase|shaping|
|decrease|shaping|
|repeat|loops|
|bind_off|finishing|
|join|combine sections|

---

# 18. Step Object Example

```json
{
  "step_id": 12,
  "type": "increase",
  "instruction": "Increase 2 stitches evenly",
  "increase_count": 2
}
```

---

# 19. Repeat Logic

Many patterns use repeated instructions.

Example:

```text
Repeat rows 4–8 six times.
```

Structured:

```json
{
  "type": "repeat_block",
  "start_row": 4,
  "end_row": 8,
  "repeat_count": 6
}
```

---

# 20. Conditional Logic

Some instructions vary by:

- size
    
- yarn
    
- style variation
    

System must support branching.

---

## Example

```json
{
  "condition": "size == XL",
  "instruction": "Add 12 stitches"
}
```

---

# 21. Multi-Size Support

Patterns may include:

- S
    
- M
    
- L
    
- XL
    

The system should:

- isolate instructions per size
    
- simplify visible instructions
    

User only sees selected size instructions.

---

# 22. Measurement System

Supports:

- cm
    
- inches
    

All internal calculations normalized.

---

# 23. Row Tracking System

Critical UX component.

Tracks:

- current row
    
- completed rows
    
- repeated cycles
    
- milestones
    

---

# 24. Smart Progress Tracking

The app understands:

- repeated blocks
    
- section completion
    
- total progress
    

